cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.CV, cs.SD

The paper presents a deep learning approach for automatic sleep staging, which involves sequence-to-sequence modeling and transfer learning. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). The paper also involves image processing techniques for sleep data analysis, which suggests a possible fit with cs.CV (Computer Vision). Finally, the paper deals with sleep data acquisition and processing, which could be related to cs.SD (Sound and Music Computing).
